headline: MarketAxess tops profit expectations as market volatility fuels record trading
summary: Bond trading platform MarketAxess beat Wall Street estimates for first-quarter profit on Wednesday, as heightened market volatility sparked record trading results. WHY IT'S IMPORTANT Sweeping changes by U.S. President Donald Trump affecting global trade policy have injected volatility in the bond markets and spurred investor engagement. MarketAxess' results offer an insight into the bond market, widely viewed as a more reliable indicator of recession than the stock market.
